	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That SRAM issue is not unique, I had the same problem with a few NES games : When the crash the saves are erased (very likely the CPU is going crazy and accidentally write into SRAM).
<br />
<br />Now to guess what causes the CPU crash I can't do it for you... if it systematically crashes at the same place this is a software error. If it crashes randomly it's more likely to be an hardware fault.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


