	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've never heard of corrupt data stopping a game from booting. Generally a game will have a checksum to determine if saved data is valid and not attempt to load that data if it fails and generally it will be erased if corrupt.
<br />
<br />No idea what your problem is though. If your ROM is translated maybe the translation doesn't work on real hardware properly.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
